Let $f_n(x)$ be defined recursively by

$ f_0(x) = x, quad f_1(x) = f(x), quad f_(n+1)(x) = f(f_n(x)), quad "for " n >= 0, $

where $f(x) = 1 + sin(x - 1)$.

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")

+ Show that there is a unique point $x_0$ such that $f_2(x_0) = x_0$.
+ Find $display(sum_(n=0)^(infinity) (f_n(x_0))/(3^n))$ with the above $x_0$.
